From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: John Kleinschmidt <jkleinsc@electronjs.org>
Date: Thu, 4 Jun 2026 10:26:11 -0400
Subject: test: guard vm contextual-store strict assertion for Chromium's V8

test-vm-global-contextual-store was added upstream in
https://github.com/nodejs/node/pull/62571. It asserts that an undeclared
strict-mode contextual store (`"use strict"; z = 42`) throws a ReferenceError.

Electron uses Chromium's V8, which removed v8::PropertyCallbackInfo<T>::This()
(https://github.com/nodejs/node/issues/60616). Without the receiver, the
contextify property setter cannot distinguish a contextual store (`z = 42`)
from an explicit `this.z = 42` store, so the undeclared strict-mode contextual
store is written to the sandbox instead of throwing. Preserving explicit global
stores (relied on by `globalThis.x = v` in vm modules, e.g.
test-vm-module-referrer-realm) matters more than this edge case, so skip the
ReferenceError assertion under Electron.

This patch can be removed once Chromium's V8 exposes the receiver again or the
contextify setter can otherwise detect a contextual store.

diff --git a/test/parallel/test-vm-global-contextual-store.js b/test/parallel/test-vm-global-contextual-store.js
index 1ae74adb541b586a99e148e8dcff39e0b613acb2..8c349cf0cc86c936da51a8f956595e608c03a48b 100644
--- a/test/parallel/test-vm-global-contextual-store.js
+++ b/test/parallel/test-vm-global-contextual-store.js
@@ -14,6 +14,13 @@ assert.strictEqual(ctx.x, 42);
 vm.runInContext('y = 42', ctx);
 assert.strictEqual(ctx.y, 42);
 
-assert.throws(() => vm.runInContext('"use strict"; z = 42', ctx),
-              /ReferenceError: z is not defined/);
-assert.strictEqual(Object.hasOwn(ctx, 'z'), false);
+// Electron uses Chromium's V8, which removed v8::PropertyCallbackInfo::This()
+// (https://github.com/nodejs/node/issues/60616). Without the receiver, the
+// contextify property setter cannot distinguish a contextual store (`z = 42`)
+// from an explicit `this.z = 42` store, so an undeclared strict-mode contextual
+// store is written to the sandbox instead of throwing a ReferenceError.
+if (!process.versions.electron) {
+  assert.throws(() => vm.runInContext('"use strict"; z = 42', ctx),
+                /ReferenceError: z is not defined/);
+  assert.strictEqual(Object.hasOwn(ctx, 'z'), false);
+}
